fields.title: Citation and Redaction
fields.content:
Now you can add citation to any kind of `write` like this: `[citation](/c)` or `[citation](/citation)`. It can be used anywhere[^1]. Just add it below a paragraph (but no line break between the paragraph and the citation):
[this is a citation I put to this paragraph](/c)

```
sometext
[citation](/c)
```

[^1]: but the effect will not apply to the feed and comment

But the best practice is putting the citation within a block quote (`>`), like this:

```
> this is a block quote
> [citation needed](/c)
```

and it will look like this:

> this is a block quote
> [citation needed](/c)

Along with citation, I also added redaction, in another word, hiding text for spoiler ( `[text](/s)` or `[text](/spoiler)`):

```
[text](/s)
```

It will look like this and you can click it to reveal it:

[spoiler alert!](/s)

#LʌvDB
I read it many years ago and I still think about it from time to time.
@jyutgeisi just brought all the good memory of reading this book back to my mind, now I am start rereading it!
